<HEADLINE>
<P>
A KINDNESS IN RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Unfortunately, it isn't very often that we take the time to write concerning 
a very nice happening in Los Angeles.However, being a New Englander (proud of 
it too), and finding so many skeptics in these parts, I must say I was 
overwhelmed the other evening. When waiting for the bus in a rare "driving 
rainstorm" at the corner of Robertson and 3rd Street, a very kind parking lot 
attendant removed his rain slicker and insisted on my wearing it home. Perhaps 
these types of things do happen in L.A., but how often do we really take the 
time to say "thank you" publicly? 
</P>
<P>
 MIL BROOKS 
</P>
<P>
 Playa del Rey 
</P>
</TEXT>
