<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR ARTS GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The L.A. County Music and Performing Arts Commission will accept applications 
through March 4 for its National/State/County Partnership 1994-95 grants. 
</P>
<P>
 The program grants dollars and technical assistance to low-budget and 
developing nonprofit arts organizations. First- and second-year grants range 
from $1,000 to $5,000; third- and fourth-year grants from $5,000 to $10,000. A 
free workshop to help applicants is scheduled today at 7 p.m. at the Ken 
Edwards Center in Santa Monica. Information: (213) 974-1343. 
</P>
