'RUSH HOUR' SHOWS GET NEW SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Igby's Comedy Cabaret, the West Los Angeles comedy club that began offering a 
free "Rush Hour Comedy Break" for commuters following the Jan. 17 earthquake, 
has scaled the program back to Thursday and Friday evenings only. 
</P>
<P>
 The free performances, by stand-up comedians who donate their time, take place 
from 5 to 7 p.m., with no cover or minimum purchase required. 
</P>
<P>
 Igby's is located at 11637 W. Pico Blvd., near the intersection of the 405 and 
10 freeways. 
</P>
