<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; JORDAN FINALLY HITS A HOME RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Jordan listened to some advice from Chicago White Sox teammate Frank 
Thomas, then finally hit a ball over the fence on his last swing of batting 
practice. It was the first time since camp began a week ago that the 6-foot-6 
Jordan had cleared the fence. 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan was asked if hitting a homer compared to making a three-pointer in 
basketball. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's something like that," he said. "But I can hit a three-pointer. And quite 
often." 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan will face live pitching from major leaguers for the first time today. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Cleveland Indians traded left-handed pitcher Shawn Bryant to the Minnesota 
Twins for a player to be determined. . . . Pitcher Bob Walk, 13-14 in 32 starts 
last season, his 14th in the major leagues, is retiring to join the Pittsburgh 
Pirates' revamped broadcast team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
