1994 PREP GOLF: SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; BREA-OLINDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Ken Lutz (fifth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1992-93: 15-3, 10-0 in the Orange League; finished 12th in the Southern 
Regional. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Jarrod Brunner, Sr.; Bob Bryant, Sr.; Paul Chiotti, Sr.; Keith 
Matsuno, Sr.; Mike Peterson, Sr.; Wayne Spurlock, Sr.; Wayne Wilson, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Kevin Creagh, Jr.; Anthony Eliason, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Last year, the Wildcats split dual matches with Sunny Hills and 
Esperanza but had a dismal performance in the Southern Regional -- three of 
their six players shot 90 or above. But all except one of their top six players 
are returning and they are all experienced seniors. "We don't have any shining 
stars, but I've got five solid guys and depending on the day, we can turn in 
some good numbers," Lutz said. All five have been with the program for four 
years. Brunner and Matsuno are three-year varsity lettermen and Peterson has 
been the team's top player for the past two years. Chiotti, quarterback on the 
football team, skipped basketball this year to concentrate on golf. Wilson 
showed the biggest improvement last year. 
