said the Sea Kings should be strong because of their even temperaments. "They 
really don't let things bother them," Donnellan said. "Every one of these kids 
is a quiet, quiet, quiet reserved individual and I think that's what you need 
for good golf. You need introspective deep thinkers and every varsity player is 
a thinker." Four players return from the team last year, and Welker played for 
the varsity the year before. Sarracino was the No. 2 player last year as a 
freshman, and Walden is being recruited by California. "We're going to be very 
competitive," Donnellan said. "I would assume so because they have all been 
there before." 
