<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Barbara Mathews 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Whitney Torregano, Magnolia's leading scorer, averaged 16.5 points in the 
Sentinels' Division III-AA playoff victories over Moreno Valley Rancho Verde 
and La Habra.Dorretha Bennem also contributed by averaging nine points and 16.5 
rebounds, but without Mathews, Magnolia wouldn't have advanced to the 
quarterfinals. Against Rancho Verde, she made five of six free throws in the 
final minute and against La Habra she made two free throws with 15 seconds left 
to give the Sentinels a 40-38 victory. Mathews scored nine points in each game. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tina Brescini, Esperanza, scored two goals in overtime to help the Aztecs to 
a 2-1 victory over Villa Park in the Division II soccer playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Shanna Renken, El Dorado, had 26 points and 11 rebounds in a 57-39 victory 
over La Quinta in the Division III-AA playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
