last year, returns one player. Coach Gary Sabella said he expects the lineup to 
include three or four sophomores and one freshman: "We're going to be a lot 
better than people think, even though we lost a lot of players." . . . 
Western's Tiger Woods accepted the Dial Award, for the nation's top boys' high 
school scholar-athlete, Jan. 15 at the Touchdown Club in Washington. The award 
came with a $5,000 donation to Western. 
</P>
