ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; SIX-WEEK COURSE ON PARENTING OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District is sponsoring a six-week course for parents 
who want to build a stronger relationship with their children. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed "Active Parenting," the course features discussions on communicating 
better with children and setting discipline and appropriate behavior as well as 
sharing of experiences among the participating parents. 
</P>
<P>
 The classes begin tonight and continue on Tuesdays through March 29 from 7 to 
9 p.m. at Barbara Benson Elementary School, 12712 Elizabeth Way. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost for the entire course is $15, which includes materials, child care and 
refreshments, according to instructor Chris Wall. 
</P>
<P>
 For registration and additional information, call (714) 730-7336. BERT ELJERA 
