<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; RETIREMENT SEMINAR TO EXAMINE FINANCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will offer a seminar on retirement tonight featuring 
discussion of financial planning and the top 20 retirement communities. 
</P>
<P>
 Nearly 80% of Americans now live beyond 65 years, and the seminar is designed 
to help those beyond retirement age maintain their financial security. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics will include comparison of home prices in various states, relocation 
costs, taxes and small-town living, spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Emphasis will be placed on the states of Arizona, Montana, Nevada, Idaho, 
Wyoming, Utah, Colorado and New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will be held from 7 to 10 p.m. in Room U-204D of the college, at 
17th and Bristol streets. There is a $20 fee for the seminar. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 564-6220.JON NALICK 
