<P>
2 UNARMED GUARDS ARE FATALLY SHOT IN ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two unarmed security guards in Orange County were shot to death within two 
hours, and investigators are trying to determine if the slayings were linked. 
</P>
<P>
 Dagoberto R. Carrero, 23, of Orange died after an 11:05 p.m. Sunday shooting 
at the Century Theater Complex at City Shopping Center, said Orange Police Lt. 
Timm Brown. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown said Carrero had confronted six teen-agers earlier in the day about 
sneaking into the theater for a 5:15 p.m. showing of "Addams Family Values," 
and one of them had threatened him. Police were searching for the teen-agers 
for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
 Carrero was shot through a lobby window as he prepared to head home to his 
wife and 9-month-old daughter, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove, Rupert Morales, 19, of Santa Ana, was shot several times in 
the parking lot of Nick's Hide Away bar at 12:50 a.m. Monday, said Garden Grove 
Police Sgt. Joe Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Morales also was an unarmed security officer, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were looking into a possible connection between the two killings, but 
had no facts to support a link, Johnson said. 
</P>
