<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; FRIEDAN IS KEYNOTE CONFERENCE SPEAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA WELDON TONE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Betty Friedan, who brought the modern women's movement to the forefront with 
her book "The Feminine Mystique," will be the keynote speaker Saturday at Cal 
Lutheran University's seminar "Creative Options, A Day for Women." 
</P>
<P>
 Held each spring on the Cal Lutheran campus, the seminar features 75 workshops 
in a range of topics.Participants are entitled to choose one workshop from each 
of three categories. The cost is $18 for the day. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to offer something for everyone, no matter what their age or stage 
of personal development," said Carol Keochekian, director of university 
relations and founder of the program. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshop topics include "Increasing Intimacy With Those We Love," "The Lesbian 
Dilemma," "How Much Does That Blouse Cost," "An Examination of Working 
Conditions for Women in the Garment Industry," "Alternative Medicine: Putting 
Your Health in Your Hands," "Networking: Schmooze or Lose," "Turn Your Next 
Interview Into a Job," "Gun Violence as a Woman's Issue," "Preparing Your 
Daughter for the 21st Century" and "Construction: Not For Men Only!" 
</P>
<P>
 Co-sponsored by the American Assn. of University Women and the Women's 
Resource Center at Cal Lutheran, the 10-year-old seminar has more than 1,000 
registrants each year. 
</P>
<P>
 "This program has become an established part of the university and its culture 
over the years," Keochekian said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to offering the seminar, Creative Options also funds a scholarship 
for re-entry women at the university. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop runs from 8 a.m to 4 p.m. at Cal Lutheran, 60 W. Olsen Road, 
Thousand Oaks. Free child care is available for children ages 3 to 9. For 
information, call the campus Women's Resource Center at 493-3345 between 9 a.m. 
and 4 p.m. BARBARA WELDON TONE 
</P>
</TEXT>
