<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTY TO AUCTION TAX-DELINQUENT LAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 County officials plan to auction 41 parcels of land Wednesday, with minimum 
bids ranging from $945 for a parcel in Lockwood Valley to $1.5 million for an 
office building in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 The tax collector has the right to auction the parcels because the landowners 
have failed to pay property taxes for more than five years. 
</P>
<P>
 Delinquent taxes from the properties total $1.3 million, according to a 
statement from the county treasurer's office. 
</P>
<P>
 "Generally, these are strange pieces of property," said Harold Pittman, county 
treasurer-tax collector. "Many times, you find you cannot build on the 
property, but it may have value to the people who own property next to it." 
</P>
<P>
 Pittman said six of the plots have structures on them. 
</P>
<P>
 The properties, located throughout Ventura County, will be auctioned off 
beginning at 9 a.m. Wednesday in the Lower Plaza Assembly Room of the 
Administration Building, County Government Center, 800 S. Victoria Ave., 
Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Only cash, cashier's checks or certified checks will be accepted, and all of 
the sales are "as is." 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call 654-3725. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
