<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; ANOTHER DAY ADDED TO COURTHOUSE HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The hours at the East County Courthouse will be expanded to include another 
full day, Ventura County Supervisor Vicky Howard announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard, who has made it her goal to increase county services in the east end 
of the county, said she was glad that Commissioner John Pattie was adding a 
third day to his current two-day schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 Pattie now hears family law cases on Mondays and Thursdays. Under the new 
schedule -- which goes into effect the week of April 4 -- he will also hear 
family law and civil cases on Fridays. 
</P>
<P>
 "Adding an extra court day and civil cases in Simi Valley means east county 
residents will not have to make the long drive to Ventura," Howard said in a 
prepared statement. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm pleased we've been able to expand our services." 
</P>
<P>
 Howard in 1992 pushed for the addition of a second court commissioner to the 
East County Courthouse. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioner David Long is also stationed at the Simi Valley facility, and 
hears Municipal Court cases every weekday except Thursdays, officials said. 
JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
