<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILDREN DESERVE A PERMANENT COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your editorial supporting the satellite children's court in the Antelope 
Valley (Jan. 30) was appreciated. 
</P>
<P>
 Your insights into the devastating effects of forcing distressed families into 
a transportation nightmare of 140-plus-mile round trips to make court 
appearances is the prime reason a permanent dependency court is required. 
</P>
<P>
 Adding insult to injury by requiring abused and neglected children to travel 
over 70 miles each way to go to court, a trip that takes two to six hours each 
day, is unconscionable. 
</P>
<P>
 We were successful in opening the satellite court in the Antelope Valley last 
July. This was a welcome relief. 
</P>
<P>
 With the recent devastating earthquake, the collapsed freeways punctuated the 
need for expanded county services in the Antelope Valley.  
</P>
<P>
 We have been working with Superior Court Judge Marcus Tucker, presiding judge 
of the Juvenile Court, to make the satellite dependency court in the Antelope 
Valley permanent. 
</P>
<P>
 MICHAEL D. ANTONOVICH 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Antonovich represents the 5th District on the Los Angeles County Board of 
Supervisors.  
</P>
