<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISTRICT DOES HAVE PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your Feb. 4 story on the Ventura County Community College District ("College 
Officials Seek Disaster Plan") states that our organization did not have an 
emergency plan in place for our students and staff. In fact, our district and 
its three colleges have had an emergency plan in place since approval by the 
Board of Trustees in 1984.This plan uses the same philosophy, approach and 
structure as the plans developed by other public entities, and each member of 
the staff has been given a copy of the plan. 
</P>
<P>
 Emergency-plan training is an ongoing activity throughout our district. In 
addition, the necessary medical and rescue materials are stored and ready for 
use at each college, and all district vehicles contain instructions on 
emergency procedures. 
</P>
<P>
 The terrible disaster on Jan. 17 did reveal, however, that our internal 
communications network requires greater refinement, and this has been a high 
priority effort since that date. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas G. Lakin 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas G. Lakin is chancellor of the Ventura County Community College 
District.  
</P>
