<HEADLINE>
<P>
HORSES NOT DONATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In reference to a story Feb. 6 about 11 starving horses "donated" to the 
Humane Society Shelter: To donate is to make a gift of, or to contribute to, a 
public or charitable cause. These horses are not a gift or contribution to the 
Humane Society of Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 California state humane officers went to the Warner Ranch with a search 
warrant and seized these abused animals as evidence. The animals were placed in 
protective custody and brought to the Humane Society Shelter. Mrs. Warner 
agreed to sign the animals over to the Humane Society to avoid prosecution. 
</P>
<P>
 The Humane Society of Ventura County is a nonprofit organization that receives 
no federal, state, county or city funding. We welcome donations. 
</P>
<P>
 Jolene Hoffman 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
<P>
 Jolene Hoffman is shelter director of the Humane Society of Ventura County.  
