<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SKI-A-THON TO RAISE FUNDS FOR COALITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Skiers will hit the slopes of Mammoth Mountain on Saturday to raise money for 
a coalition against youth crime and a scholarship fund in memory of slain 
teen-ager Steve Woods. 
</P>
<P>
 The First Annual Steve Woods Ski-a-Thon will be held at Mammoth Mountain Ski 
Resort from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. A registration fee of $24 includes a T-shirt and 
barbecue.Prizes will be awarded to winners of the ski race. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods, 17, died Nov. 9, about three weeks after his head was pierced by a 
metal paint roller rod during a confrontation with alleged gang members and 
their friends or associates at Calafia County Beach Park in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 The high school senior loved to ski with family and friends and celebrated his 
birthday each February with a trip to Mammoth Mountain. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ski-a-Thon is sponsored in part by Athletes for Youth, a nonprofit group 
formed by broadcaster and former professional football player Todd Christensen 
to prevent youth crime and substance abuse. The organizers, including Woods' 
mother and sister, hope to make it into an annual event. 
</P>
<P>
 Said Liz Lee with Athletes for Youth: "All you need is your ski gear, your 
friends and lots of sponsors who pledge to support your efforts on the slopes." 
</P>
<P>
 For information about entry fees, lift tickets, sponsorship forms and other 
information, call (714) 541-9369 during the day or (714) 443-9482 at night. 
ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</TEXT>
