<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
111 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fluor Chief Has Prostate Cancer: The Irvine-based engineering concern said Les 
McCraw, its chairman and chief executive, will undergo surgery March 2.Fluor 
spokeswoman Kirsten Frosh said the tumor is small and contained and that "it 
was caught in the very early stages of development." McCraw, 59, is expected to 
return to work two weeks after the surgery. He was named CEO of Fluor in 1990 
and assumed the additional title of chairman the following year. He has worked 
for the engineering giant since 1975. After suffering a string of losses in the 
early and mid-1980s, Fluor posted record revenue of $7.9 billion for 1993, with 
earnings of $166.8 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
