<TEXT>
<P>
 Ford Announces Recalls: The company is recalling about 16,400 1992 and 1993 
Crown Victoria cars used by police, taxi companies and other fleets because of 
a wiring problem that could cause a fire under the front seats. It is also 
recalling about 400,000 1993 and 1994 F-Series pickup trucks and Broncos. The 
auto maker said the vehicles' front bumpers could be jarred loose because of 
faulty nuts fastening the bumpers to the vehicles. 
</P>
