<TEXT>
<P>
 Motorola Develops Multimedia Option for PCs: Instead of using add-on cards to 
give sound and video capabilities to personal computers, the new Motorola 
product uses software developed around a single chip, called a digital signal 
processor, or DSP. The product, called PC Media, will be available to makers of 
personal computers and software writers. The technology allows the DSP chips to 
run voice and sound for entertainment as well as a fax, modem or telephone. 
</P>
