<P>
ENERGY CONTAINER OF SANTA ANA PURCHASED BY CANADIAN FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Bloomberg Business News 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Derlan Industries Ltd. said it has agreed to buy Energy Container Corp., a 
closely held Santa Ana company that makes fuel tanks for aircraft. No purchase 
price was disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Energy Container employs 105 people and has annual sales of about $16 million. 
The company also makes valves for the petrochemical industry. 
</P>
<P>
 In connection with the acquisition, "Derlan will consolidate three of its 
California operations, together with Energy Container, into one large plant," 
Derlan said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other three plants are located within a roughly 20-mile radius of the 
Energy Container plant, said Michael Forsayeth, vice president and chief 
financial officer of Toronto-based Derlan. 
</P>
<P>
 The closing of the three plants will result in a small charge, "but we don't 
expect it's going to cost a ton of money," Forsayeth said. He declined to be 
more specific. 
</P>
