community was developed and researched by Times special correspondents Susan 
Byrnes and Kurt Pitzer. The interviews were conducted by special correspondents 
Byrnes, Kay Hwangbo, Geoffrey Mohan, Pitzer and Jeannette Regalado. They 
interviewed several dozen people, and point out that while the voices do not 
represent all of the 73,851 African Americans who make up 4% of the Valley's 
population, the diversity of the ideas presented demonstrates a wide range of 
goals and hopes expressed. 
</P>
