<P>
4 HELD IN JEWELRY STORE HEIST-SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies arrested three men and one teen-ager Monday for last week's 
slaying of a jewelry store employee, who was shot in the upper chest during a 
robbery, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested were Tyrran Delvon Wilson, 20; Walter Lenard Johnson, 19; Antonio Lee 
Roberts, 20; and a 16-year-old boy; all from Palmdale, according to Deputy 
Larry Mead of the Sheriff's Headquarters Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
 Last Friday, deputies responded to a 911 call at 1:11 p.m. from a passerby who 
looked into Charles Jewelers at 38513 Sierra Hwy. and saw smashed display 
cases.  
</P>
<P>
 When authorities arrived, they found 45-year-old Sung Heeh Hwang lying on the 
floor, Mead said. Hwang had been working alone. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have not released an estimated value of the jewelry taken during 
the robbery. ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
</P>
