<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 KILLED IN CRASH OF CARGO HELICOPTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A cargo helicopter returning from a lifting job flipped out of control and 
slammed into a soggy suburban hillside Monday, killing all three people aboard. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims were employees of San Jose-based Air One Helicopters, which owned 
the twin-engine Sikorsky S-58T helicopter. One victim had escaped injury last 
month when an identical Air One helicopter crashed into a San Jose rooftop, 
killing the pilot. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims' names were being withheld pending notification of their families. 
</P>
