NATION IN BRIEF; FLORIDA; 2 HELD IN DEATH OF MAN, RAPE OF SISTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were charged with murder and rape for an attack on a brother and 
sister they had befriended during a camping trip, police said.The brother was 
beaten to death, and the sister was raped twice while she was held captive 
overnight in a tent, police said. The men left the sister tied between two 
trees, but she escaped by chewing through the cords. William Christopher Paul, 
20, and Loran K. Cole, 27, were arrested and charged with first-degree murder 
and two counts each of armed kidnaping, armed sexual battery and grand auto 
theft, according to Sgt. Joe Cobb, a spokesman for the Marion County Sheriff's 
