<P>
 One driver shot and killed another with a crossbow after the two cut each 
other off in traffic, state police said.Donald Graham, 54, of Woonsocket, R.I., 
was arrested at home and charged with murder. His wife, Sandra Graham, 51, who 
was a passenger, was arrested and charged as an accessory, prosecutor John 
Letourneau said. The victim was identified as Michael Blodgett, 42, of 
Attleboro. The drivers had been cutting each other off and flashing their 
headlights as they drove down Interstate 95, Trooper Dermot Moriarty said. When 
the drivers pulled over, both left their cars. Police said Graham took a 
