</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Superior Industries International Inc., a Van Nuys supplier of cast aluminum 
wheels to auto manufacturers, reported strong earnings gains for its fourth 
quarter and year that ended Dec. 31.It attributed the increases to growth in 
passenger and light trucks, expanding market share and operating efficiencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's fourth-quarter profit was $12.6 million, up 36% from $9.24 
million in net income a year earlier. Its revenue rose 14%, to $105.2 million 
from $92.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the full year, Superior's earnings jumped 58% to $45.2 million from $28.6 
million in 1992. Its annual revenue in 1993 was $393 million, a 20% gain from 
$325.3 million in the previous year. 
