<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: KENFIL INC. POSTS 70% DROP IN SECOND-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kenfil Inc., a Van Nuys computer software distributor, reported a 70% drop in 
profit for its fiscal second-quarter that ended Dec. 31, and said its losses 
from the Northridge earthquake Jan. 17 could amount to $3 million to $4 
million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the second quarter, Kenfil earned $72,000 compared with a profit of 
$237,000 in the same period a year earlier.Fiscal second-quarter revenue 
totaled $49.9 million, about the same as a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Earnings for the six months that ended Dec. 31 fell 64% to $181,000, from 
$505,000 for the same period a year earlier. Its latest six-month revenue 
increased 8% to $96.5 million, from $89.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it expected soon to announce plans for a restructuring and 
consolidation of warehouse operations. Kenfil said it expected to take a charge 
of about $700,000 in the quarter that ends March 31 for expenses related to the 
restructuring. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the company said the earthquake halted operations for about two 
weeks and destroyed several million dollars of inventory. The company is now 
fully operational. 
</P>
