<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: AMWEST INSURANCE INCOME UP 24% IN FOURTH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amwest Insurance Group Inc., a Woodland Hills-based firm that specializes in 
surety bonds, reported a 24% increase in its fourth-quarter net income after 
premiums written increased 34% to record levels. 
</P>
<P>
 Amwest said its profit for the quarter that ended Dec. 31 came to $1.18 
million, up from $954,000 a year earlier. Premiums written, a figure comparable 
to revenue, surged to $14.7 million, from $11 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the year that ended Dec. 31, Amwest's net income rose 11% to $3.79 
million, from $3.4 million for 1992. Premiums written in 1993 totaled $57.7 
million, up 14% from $50.5 million in 1992. 
