<P>
CHAD THERAPEUTICS REPORTS PROFIT SURGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chad Therapeutics, a Chatsworth maker of oxygen-conserving devices used by 
patients with respiratory problems, said its fiscal third-quarter profit surged 
71% on nearly as big a jump in sales. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months ended Dec. 31, Chad earned $524,831, compared with 
$306,965 a year earlier. Sales rose 61%, to $2.5 million from $1.5 million in 
Chad's 1992 fiscal third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first nine months of fiscal 1993, Chad's net income rose 62% to $1.5 
million from $917,946 in the same period a year ago. Sales climbed 66% to $6.9 
million from $4.2 million. 
