<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: NESEN PLANS TO OPEN ROLLS-ROYCE DEALERSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Is Ventura County a Rolls-Royce market? 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Nesen, president and chief executive of Thousand Oaks' Nesen Motor Car 
Co., thinks so. 
</P>
<P>
 Early next month, his firm will become the county's only retailer of Rolls and 
its sister British import, the Bentley. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've done marketing studies, and we expect to do well in Westlake Village, 
Thousand Oaks and in the western county as well," Nesen said. "We haven't set a 
sales target, but we're starting out with two Rolls and three Bentleys." 
</P>
<P>
 The cars are priced from $147,000 to as high as $337,000 for a Rolls 
limousine. 
</P>
<P>
 Nesen, who has eight other dealerships, is adding yet another luxury car line, 
the Excalibur, which sells for $55,000 to $65,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Almost all buyers of these cars will be business owners, doctors, lawyers or 
movie people, Nesen expects. "We consider Malibu and the Valley to be part of 
our marketing area. Almost half our sales already come from those areas." 
</P>
</TEXT>
